    narr:narration """A mixed hub gathering the moments Scarlet flagged as inflections — strategic, market, and tactical. The dominant frame is [base camp, not camp 4](narr:Narrative_BaseCampNotCamp4): the the enterprise customer pilot's week-1 surge (8/16 engaging, license expansion 2→7→16, MSA to lawyer) flips the question from acquisition to customer success — real inflection, long climb (May 18). Against that sits a closing-window counter-clock: Tony's [two-year window](narr:Narrative_TwoYearWindow) before legal pressure reshapes LLMs toward approved sources. Macro signal echoes it — [enterprise budget reallocation](narr:Observation_InflectionPoints_1) as SaaS incumbents sell off on disintermediation fears. A distinct product-model thread: the [optometrist convergence](narr:Observation_ConvergenceInsight), where Scarlet's misremembered task resolved into the review flow itself, plus the [parallel-temporality articulation](narr:Obs_ScarletTemporalityQuote) (May 1). Tactical residue clusters separately: the [live-transcription question](narr:Obs_LiveTranscriptionQuestion) (Fireflies post-call only), its [BlackHole + MacWhisper answer](narr:Claim_BlackHoleMacWhisper) still open, and three [quick wins](narr:Observation_QuickWins). The digest holds these on parallel tracks rather than one arc.""" ;
